&lt;p&gt;Taskrabbit is a hybrid company with employees distributed across the US and EU and a Built In — Best Places to Work (2022, 2023, 2024, 2025) continually ranked across multiple national and regional categories. Join us at Taskrabbit, where your work will be meaningful, your ideas valued, and your potential unleashed!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a hybrid role that will sit out of our San Francisco office. Hybrid in-office Tuesdays and Wednesdays of each week.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a hands-on builder to lead our ‘AI for Work’ efforts. This role is focused exclusively on internal operations — there is no external product work. Reporting to the Director of AI Strategy and Enablement, you will embed directly within our business functions, map and reimagine how work gets done, and build the AI agents, automations, and internal tools that make our teams dramatically more efficient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will execute without a dedicated engineering partner. The right candidate has shipped Claude-powered workflows, agents, and automations in a professional context and can do it again here — independently, scrappily, and fast. Beyond building, you will help each function develop the capability to identify and build their own AI solutions over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discover &amp;amp; diagnose: &lt;/strong&gt;Embed with business teams across functions to map end-to-end workflows, surface high-impact automation opportunities, and redesign work from first principles — not just automate existing steps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build: &lt;/strong&gt;Independently design, build, and deploy Claude-powered agents, automations, and internal tools that eliminate repetitive work and improve output quality and consistency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Measure: &lt;/strong&gt;Establish baselines before every intervention; define and track the right business metrics for each function (e.g. time saved, error rate) to validate real impact, not just adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enable: &lt;/strong&gt;Train and enable non-technical teams to identify, scope, and eventually build their own automations — building durable capability within functions, not dependency on this role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Influence: &lt;/strong&gt;Serve as a trusted translator between business problems and technical solutions; partner with senior leaders to align automation priorities with company OKRs and drive change with skeptical or resistant stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scale: &lt;/strong&gt;Build reusable patterns and playbooks so successful automations in one function can be adapted and scaled across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;2+

